$interpreted: Patrolling Archer: Another peaceful day on the job...

Patrolling Soldier: What do you expect? This is the border between Paradise Prairie and Atlas. 
No sane person would visit a place with monsters everywhere for no reason.
Patrolling Archer: Hey, after our shift is done, a drink or two at the pub?
Patrolling Soldier: Sure. This time, I'll definitely...
Patrolling Archer: Hm? Who is that?
Tica: Hello~ I'm Tica of Rune Academy. I want to go check out Atlas.
Patrolling Soldier: Rune Academy? Is it a mission?
Patrolling Archer: But we didn't receive any papers...is there something important you have to do in Atlas?
Tica: Of course. I'm going to have an adventure in Atlas. A way to prove my strength~
Tica: As well as an opportunity to get some fun stories to brag about to other folks!
Patrolling Soldier: Then it's nothing important! Scram, now. Atlas isn't a place for you to mess around!
Patrolling Archer: Yeah, little girl. If you get scared and crap your pants inside, no one will be there to save you.
Tica: Eeh~ But my talent for rune magic is even acknowledged by Headmaster Ceres. It's probably going to be a-ok, right?
Patrolling Soldier: I don't give a damn about some random headmaster. Get lost! We're not working overtime for your mess!

Patrolling Archer: You don't look very reliable. No idea why that headmaster would even compliment you. 
My guess is that he isn't too bright himself either!
Tica: You little...it's irritating when you look down on me, but how DARE you insult Headmaster Ceres as well!
Tica: I'll show you losers what I'm capable of! Eat this!
Tica: Hmph, now you know how awesome I am. So, Tica will be on her way. Adiós~
Patrolling Soldier: Hey, wait a minute!
Tica: What, up for round two? I definitely won't go easy on you this time!
Patrolling Soldier: No, I just want to remind you to be careful.
Tica: Be careful of what?
Patrolling Archer: For the past few months, we've been hearing this really eerie singing coming from Atlas.
Patrolling Archer: This is not a known habit of the monsters, which makes it really frightening.
Patrolling Soldier: If it's a monster, we can kill it. But, if it's a ghost or a spirit, we've no idea what to do.
Patrolling Soldier: Therefore, nobody is willing to even go near that. We advise you don't take the risk.
Tica: Eerie singing...ghosts or spirits...
Tica: ...Sounds like so much fun!
Patrolling Soldier: What!?
Tica: Let me handle the investigation. I promise that you guys can patrol safely in the future.
Tica: No longer will you have to be troubled by that weird singing.
Patrolling Soldier: No, that's not what we meant. You shouldn't...
Tica: No need to worry for me. Here I come, creepy singing voices~!
Patrolling Archer: What now?
Patrolling Soldier: Just pretend nothing happened.
Patrolling Soldier: If our superiors know that we couldn't even handle a little girl, we'll be in all kinds of trouble...
Patrolling Archer: Guess that's the best we can do for now...
